Mohonasen High School is excited to announce that the Mohonasen Awards for Media Arts will be aired on the Mohonasen High School YouTube Channel at 8 p.m. on June 11.

This event will recognize the outstanding work being done by students in the field of video production by the school‚Äôs Live Production and Media Arts students.

The awards ceremony was originally slated to be held at the Bowtie Cinema in Rotterdam Square Mall. We look forward to returning to that venue for the 2021 Mohonasen Awards for Media Arts ceremonies.

post_text: This group of Draper 8th graders isn't letting a pandemic slow them down. After winning their division at the Odyssey of the Mind Regionals a couple months ago, they were disappointed when the NY State competition was cancelled. When the opportunity came up to participate in a Virtual World Finals for Odyssey of the Mind, they jumped at the chance. They submitted a video of their regionals Long Term Problem performance, along with additional commentary. They also recently participated in a virtual Spontaneous Problem via a Zoom conference call. During that call, they created answers to a verbal question and submitted their most creative responses, all in a short period of time. Their coaches could not be more proud, and the team is awaiting the results, which will be announced at the end of May.

Mohonasen CSD added 34 new photos.
December 5, 2019 at 9:05 PM ¬∑

After 25 rounds, Draper eighth-grader Alexandra Greenwood placed first in the annual Draper Spelling Bee by correctly spelling the word distal.

She and eighth-grader Spencer Pease went toe-to-toe for several rounds before Alex took the crown, taking turns spelling words such as unquenchable, diaphoresis, visite, levees, gallium, Giza, jodhpurs and divan. Spencer is the school's runner-up.

Alex now advances to the regional bee, which will take place this year on Tuesday, Feb. 4 at Proctors Theatre in Schenectady. The regional bee is held annually and determines which students from the Capital Region will travel to the nation's capital in the Scripps National Spelling Bee.

Best of luck to Alex and congratulations to all of our top spellers at Draper!

post_text: Last month, Ms. Erica Restifo's developmental skills class partnering with the Work-Based Learning program, took a field trip to Graham's Coffee Parlor on State Street in Schenectady. Owner Katryn Malen, a member of the Mohonasen Business Advisory, showed students around her business, teaching them valuable lessons on customer service, safety and communication. She also gave students advice on how to be a quality barista for the district's Coffee Cart project. Thanks for being a part of the Mohon Family! #mohonproud

Each month, the music department chooses a group of Shining Stars to recognize for positive behavior and constant good effort. These students come prepared, work hard and have a good attitude. They are role models to their peers, and not only talented in their musical skills, but exhibit respect for the classroom, peers and teacher.

The following students were selected for September and October: Jenna Stewart (AP music theory), Michael French (music theory), Dylan Smith (music production, year 2), Abigail Black (music production, year 1), Julia French (concert band), D'Sean Madison-Key (high school choir), Mary Kathryn Conway (high school orchestra), Anthonly Napoli (choir), Zoe Thomas (orchestra), Amanda Strauss (band), Anthony Gagliardi (music theory), Charles Woodward (music production.)

Thank you to everyone who has supported MohonCARES this year. Your contributions have made a big difference in meeting the basic food, clothing and supply needs of our students. Consider us #MohonProud

If you are not already familiar with the facets of MohonCARES at the different levels you can access some general information here: Read more about the program here: https://www.mohonasen.org/student-services/mohoncares/

For those of you who have donated via a credit card as opposed to via payroll deduction, or for those of you who were planning on doing so, please be aware that we have shifted to GoFundMe to help collect electronic donations. You can access our page below to make a donation by credit card.

Donors may also continue to send checks payable to the Mohonasen Central School District, mailed to Attn: Tracey Freemantle, 2072 Curry Road, Schenectady, NY, 12303.

If you have any questions about the program or making a donation, please contact Alissa Ouderkirk at aouderkirk@mohonasen.org or 518-356-8250.
